solution: ```class Solution {
    public long mostPoints(int[][] questions) {
        int n = questions.length;
        long[] dp = new long[n + 1];
        for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
            int points = questions[i][0], brainpower = questions[i][1];
            int next = Math.min(i + brainpower + 1, n);
            dp[i] = Math.max(dp[i + 1], points + dp[next]);
        }
        return dp[0];
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Bottom-up DP scans the array once from right to left, storing the best score reachable from each index. Each state only depends on later states, so the recurrence is O(1) per index.

